The paper deals with complexity theory and the study of the relationships between different complexity classes. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implications of these relationships for cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), logic (cs.LO), and information theory (cs.IT).
